CBRE, as the exclusive sales agent, is pleased to present 170 Pacific Highway, St Leonards. Situated just 
moments from St Leonards Station and Crows Nest town centre, this trophy freehold building comprises five-storeys of newly refurbished offices. Currently fully leased with a long WALE of 4+ years, 170 Pacific Highway is also DA approved for an additional two storeys of office space. Accordingly, the property is a secure investment with significant value-add potential, further capitalising from its location within a rapidly growing commercial precinct. 

170 Pacific Highway benefits from the following key attributes:

- Net income: $2,699,017 per annum*
- 100% leased with WALE of 4+ years
- NLA of 4,402sqm* plus 116 car spaces
- Five-storey freehold office building sitting on huge 2,434sqm* land parcel
- Over $2,600,000 CAPEX invested since 2015
- DA approved for an additional two storeys (NLA 1,670sqm*)
- Views of Sydney CBD and Sydney Harbour
- Set to benefit from future developments within the St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct
- Easy walk to St Leonards Station and Royal North Shore Hospital
- 4-Star NABERS Energy rating

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the purchase of 170 Pacific Highway, St Leonards by Wednesday, 1 July 2020 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate
Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

CBRE and PropertyFox are pleased to present 110-112 Christie Street, St Leonards to the market. This outstanding freehold office building boasts three storeys of commercial space plus parking for 38 cars and is currently fully leased to Australia’s market leader in the television and digital media industry, Fremantle. Situated adjacent to the existing St Leonards Station and a short walk to the future Crows Nest Metro, the property is set to capitalise on the rapidly growing priority precinct; positioning it as a premium office investment with future development potential.

110-112 Christie Street benefits from the following key attributes:
•	Leased to multinational company, Fremantle, who have tenanted the property for over 20 years
•	Net passing income: $1,076,754 per annum*
•	Seven year lease expiring 2024
•	Three storey freehold office building with 1,608sqm* of NLA
•	38 car spaces
•	Generous breakout areas – 3 outdoor balconies plus a 195sqm* decked rooftop entertainment area
•	Substantial depreciation benefits due to capital works in 2007 and 2018
•	Additional FSR and height limit controls proposed in the St Leonards & Crows Nest 2036 Draft Plan
•	Located within the rapidly growing St Leonards and Crows Nest Station priority precinct
•	Situated adjacent to St Leonards Station and a short walk from the future Crows Nest Metro Station
•	1.5-Star NABERS Energy rating

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the acquisition of 110-112 Christie Street, St Leonards by Wednesday, 27 February 2019 at 4:00pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

*Approximate

Note: All financial figures have been provided by the Vendor. Purchasers are advised to conduct their own independent due diligence.

Positioned within the St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct and just a three minute’ walk to St Leonards Station, 120 Christie Street is a secure investment with future development potential.

120 Christie Street benefits from the following key attributes:

- Net income: $624,088 per annum*
- 100% leased to four whole-floor tenants with 4.57 year* WALE
- Newly refurbished building with strong depreciation benefits - over $1.7 million in CAPEX invested
- Four storey freehold office building with 1,154sqm* of NLA
- 10 secure basement car spaces
- Set to benefit from future developments within the St Leonards/Crows Nest priority precinct
- Further development potential within draft master plan (STCA)
- Adjoining St Leonards Train Station
- 4.4km* from Sydney CBD
- 5-Star NABERS Energy rating

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the purchase of 120 Christie Street, St Leonards by Wednesday, 25 March 2020 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.

CBRE and Knight Frank as the exclusive marketing agents, are pleased to offer 19-33 Chandos Street, St Leonards For Sale via an International Expressions of Interest campaign. The property represents an outstanding mixed-use development site at St Leonards.

19-33 Chandos Street, St Leonards offers prospective developers the opportunity to capitalise on the following features:

- Located within St Leonards CBD and part of the Draft St Leonards and Crows Nest 2036 Plan;
- Significant redevelopment potential (STCA);
- 1,649.6sqm* site area and with a 46.3 metre* street frontage;
- Uncompromised position, moments from Crows Nest Village strip shopping centre;
- 200 metres* from St Leonards Train Station;
- 400 metres* from Crows Nest Metro Train Station;
- Less than 5 kilometres* to the Sydney CBD;
- Gross Passing Income: $1,783,314.85 (Ex. GST) per annum*;
- 4.5 star NABERS Rating for 25-33 Chandos Street; and
- North facing district views.

The site will be sold via an International Expressions of Interest campaign closing Thursday 7 November 2019 at 3:00pm (AEDT).

*Approximate and based on information provided by the Vendor

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present 92 Chandos Street, St Leonards.  Situated just metres from Crows Nest Village and a short walk to St Leonards Station and the future Metro, 92 Chandos Street is a fully leased newly refurbished, three-storey commercial freehold building.  In an elevated position, 92 Chandos Street enjoys a north facing aspect with district views over  Naremburn. On the ground floor, the main entrance is off Chandos Street with the secure car park with parking for  12 cars accessed off Henry Lane. The tenant has recently undergone a significant fitout to the building providing a high end, modern office space.  This blue-chip investment is 100% fully leased to long standing, award winning tenant, Strata Choice, on a 3+3 year lease.

92 Chandos Street, St Leonards benefits from the following key attributes:
- Net Income: $359,074.74 per annum* with desirable lease terms
- Building area of 638sqm* with dual street frontages and 12 secure car spaces accessed from the rear lane
- Newly refurbished three storey freehold commercial building with development upside (STCA)
- 100% leased to long standing award winning tenant, Strata Choice, on a 3+3 year lease
- Set to benefit from the rapid growth of the St Leonards and Crows Nest 2036  Final Plan
- Situated metres from Crows Nest Village, St Leonards station and future Crows Nest Metro Station
- Future development upside under the St Leonards & Crows Nest 2036 Final Plan (STCA)
- Benefiting from no car parking levies

*Approximate

Interested parties are invited to submit their expressions of interest for the purchase of 92 Chandos Street, St Leonards by Wednesday, 2 December 2020 at 4pm.

For more information or to request access to the due diligence room, please contact the exclusive selling agents.
